\par \tab \tab CHAIRPERSON CRAWFORD:  And that is a very good point, but it might be interesting to see what commonalities they have.  Then as far as Nicholas' comment, I guess I agree.  For most statistical things, a five percent error is acceptable.  But for EIA data, depending on how they are used, my gut instinct is that may be a little bit large, because they are used in sophisticated ways, propagated through models.  
